    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - ENGINE ELECTRICAL - Removal - Main Engine Wiring Harness</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26510.3.13" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Main Engine Wiring Harness</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, disconnect the main battery negative terminal before
                    disconnecting or connecting electrical components.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The electrical harness assembly does not need to be disconnected from the relay, unless the
                    harness or relay is being replaced. Instead, two relay mounting bolts or three relay bracket bolts
                    may be removed from the valve cover.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect ground (-) cable from battery.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651044" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd09/d0987a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Glow plug relay terminals</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">To glow plug and ECM X1</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">To ECM X1</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">To battery (with fusible link)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">To ground</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect electrical connections from glow plug relay terminals.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If not removed, remove ECM and IDM assembly from support bracket .</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect main harness from sensors .</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove wiring harness clamps that secure wiring harness to cylinder heads and front cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect electrical connectors from fuel injectors and glow plug harness assemblies.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove ground wire attached at the left side of the rear of the intake manifold.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully lift main harness assembly from engine.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not tug on wiring harnesses; if resistance is felt, find the problem
                    and free connectors or clips.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
